<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/9–1140:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-11T18:00:00-04:00">September 11, 1940—6 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:30
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>48. For General Strong. The Government of Paraguay is in full
                                    agreement in connection with the despatch of a special
                                    photographic airplane from United States Territory. Details
                                    regarding a base for the expedition and laboratory facilities
                                    now available in Paraguay will be furnished later.
                                    Christian.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>